<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1509,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,318,1509,1534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Distribution (</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[318,420,1509,1534]" captionStart="FIGURES 132 – 134" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[224,1361,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[224,1362,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 132 – 134. Hephathus spp., distribution maps: 132 ― H. nanus (Herrich-Schäffer); 133 ― H. freyi (Fieber); 134 ― H. achilleae Mityaev." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244513/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">
Fig. 
<number box="[374,420,1510,1534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="133.0">133</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mediterranean (
<collectingCountry box="[627,695,1509,1534]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Spain</collectingCountry>
, Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[823,902,1510,1533]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">France</collectingCountry>
, North Africa), Transcaucasia, 
<collectingCountry box="[1271,1319,1510,1533]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Iran</collectingCountry>
, Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,244,1545,1570]" name="Ukraine" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, steppes and semideserts of South-East of European 
<collectingCountry box="[834,911,1545,1570]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[923,1057,1545,1570]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, and Central Asia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1509,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1581,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Species identification.</emphasis>
The species was described from Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[949,1013,1581,1606]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1131,1581,1606]" name="Grenada" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Granada</collectingCountry>
). Identification is based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Fieber" box="[151,307,1617,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refString="Fieber, F. X. (1868) Europaische neue oder wenig bekannte Bythoscopida. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 18, 449 - 464." type="journal article" year="1868">
Fieber (
<number box="[241,299,1617,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="1868.0">1868</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribaut" box="[369,528,1617,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refString="Ribaut, H. (1952) Homopteres Auchenorhynques. II (Jassidae). Faune de France, 57, 1 - 474." type="journal article" year="1952">
Ribaut (
<number box="[462,520,1617,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="1952.0">1952</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and on investigation of specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1076,1617,1642]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Spain</collectingCountry>
, Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1280,1618,1641]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1295,1381,1617,1642]" name="Tunisia" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,252,1654,1677]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[270,357,1653,1678]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1763,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,224,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80 ― Hephathus nanus (Herrich-Schäffer), lateral view, specimen from Bavaria; 81 – 82 ― H. achilleae Mityaev, same (81 ― specimen from North Caucasus, 82 ― specimen from Moscow Area); 83 – 94 ― H. freyi (Fieber), same (83 – 84 ― specimens from Iran, 85 ― specimen from Morocco, 86 ― specimen from West Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan, 87 – 88 ― specimens from Southern European Russia, 89 – 94 ― specimens from Kekemeren River Valley, Central Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 95 – 97 ― H. orientalis Linnavuori (95 ― lateral view, 96 ― face, 97 ― labels)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244511/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">
Fig. 
<number box="[326,357,1653,1678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="85.0">85</number>
</figureCitation>
). Identification of 
<taxonomicName box="[575,749,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tshakaranus">
<emphasis box="[575,749,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">H. tshakaranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the original description. Since the members of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,272,1689,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Hephathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are indistinguishable in genitalia shape, description of coloration is enough for species identification, and reinvestigation of 
<typeStatus box="[402,461,1726,1750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">types</typeStatus>
cannot give more information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="541" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1509,2038]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,536]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="541" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1761,1786]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[331,511,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tshakaranus">
<emphasis box="[331,511,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">H. tshakaranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on four females from the midlands of North-Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,288,1797,1822]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[305,394,1797,1822]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" unit="m" value="1850.0">1850 m</quantity>
above sea level) ca. 
<quantity box="[640,714,1797,1822]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" unit="km" value="25.0">25 km</quantity>
from the boundary with 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1116,1797,1822]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[1133,1300,1797,1822]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refString="Dlabola, J. (1957) Die Zikaden Afghanistans (Homopt. - Auchenorrhyncha) nach den Ergebnissen der von Herrn J. Klapperich in der Jahren 1952 - 1953 nach Afghanistan unternomminen Expeditionen. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 47, 265 - 303." type="journal article" year="1957">
Dlabola, 
<number box="[1240,1300,1797,1822]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="1957.0">1957</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This form differs from European 
<taxonomicName box="[408,493,1834,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[408,493,1834,1858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">H. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in darker coloration (Fig. 
<number box="[792,821,1833,1858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="68.0">68</number>
) and larger size: body length of females from the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1436,1834,1858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">type</typeStatus>
series is 4.1–4.3 mm, whereas in three other species it ranges 2.8–3.6 mm in males and 3.3–4.0 in females. Specimens agreeing with Dlabola's description of 
<taxonomicName box="[727,901,1905,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tshakaranus">
<emphasis box="[727,901,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">H. tshakaranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1080,1193,1905,1930]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1206,1335,1906,1930]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
(Central Tien Shan), 
<collectingCountry box="[293,338,1942,1965]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[398,496,1941,1966]" name="Armenia" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Armenia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tishechkin" box="[513,714,1941,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refString="Tishechkin, D. Y. (2000) Review of the species of the genus Hephathus Ribaut, 1952 (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Macropsinae) from the territory of Russia with notes on other Palaearctic species of the genus. Russian Entomological Journal, 8 (4), 239 - 252. [for 1999]" type="journal article" year="2000">
Tishechkin, 
<number box="[655,714,1942,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="2000.2002">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tishechkin" box="[728,789,1942,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" refString="Tishechkin, D. Y. (2002) A contribution to the taxonomy of leafhoppers of the subfamily Macropsinae (Homoptera, Cicadellidae) from the Eastern Palaearctic region. Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 81 (11), 1329 - 1337. [in Russian with English summary, English translation: Entomological Review, 82 (9), 1265 - 1273 (2002)]" type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
). On average, specimens from these localities are larger than 
<taxonomicName box="[206,291,1978,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[206,291,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">H. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[468,543,1977,2002]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Russia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[598,732,1977,2002]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
; e.g. in population from Central Tien Shan (Lower Suu-Samyr and Kekemeren River Valleys, 
<figureCitation box="[498,632,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1763,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,224,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80 ― Hephathus nanus (Herrich-Schäffer), lateral view, specimen from Bavaria; 81 – 82 ― H. achilleae Mityaev, same (81 ― specimen from North Caucasus, 82 ― specimen from Moscow Area); 83 – 94 ― H. freyi (Fieber), same (83 – 84 ― specimens from Iran, 85 ― specimen from Morocco, 86 ― specimen from West Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan, 87 – 88 ― specimens from Southern European Russia, 89 – 94 ― specimens from Kekemeren River Valley, Central Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 95 – 97 ― H. orientalis Linnavuori (95 ― lateral view, 96 ― face, 97 ― labels)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244511/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="540">
Figs. 
<number box="[560,632,2014,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="540" value="91.5" valueMax="94.0" valueMin="89.0">89–94</number>
</figureCitation>
) body length is 3.3–3.7 mm in males and 3.9–4.2 in females; specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[214,259,152,175]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,414,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1763,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,224,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80 ― Hephathus nanus (Herrich-Schäffer), lateral view, specimen from Bavaria; 81 – 82 ― H. achilleae Mityaev, same (81 ― specimen from North Caucasus, 82 ― specimen from Moscow Area); 83 – 94 ― H. freyi (Fieber), same (83 – 84 ― specimens from Iran, 85 ― specimen from Morocco, 86 ― specimen from West Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan, 87 – 88 ― specimens from Southern European Russia, 89 – 94 ― specimens from Kekemeren River Valley, Central Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 95 – 97 ― H. orientalis Linnavuori (95 ― lateral view, 96 ― face, 97 ― labels)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244511/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Figs. 
<number box="[342,414,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="83.5" valueMax="84.0" valueMin="83.0">83–84</number>
</figureCitation>
) are even larger: 3.3–3.8 mm and 4.2–4.7 mm, respectively. However, in all populations, from which we have a sufficient sample, specimens with light coloration as in European 
<taxonomicName box="[1209,1297,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[1209,1297,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are present together with dark coloured ones fitting the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[810,982,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tshakaranus">
<emphasis box="[810,982,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. tshakaranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[998,1136,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1763,1786]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,224,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1742]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 97. 80 ― Hephathus nanus (Herrich-Schäffer), lateral view, specimen from Bavaria; 81 – 82 ― H. achilleae Mityaev, same (81 ― specimen from North Caucasus, 82 ― specimen from Moscow Area); 83 – 94 ― H. freyi (Fieber), same (83 – 84 ― specimens from Iran, 85 ― specimen from Morocco, 86 ― specimen from West Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan, 87 – 88 ― specimens from Southern European Russia, 89 – 94 ― specimens from Kekemeren River Valley, Central Tien Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 95 – 97 ― H. orientalis Linnavuori (95 ― lateral view, 96 ― face, 97 ― labels)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244511/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Figs. 
<number box="[1062,1136,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="91.5" valueMax="94.0" valueMin="89.0">89–94</number>
</figureCitation>
). Moreover, in large series of males from Kulyab, 
<collectingCountry box="[419,529,260,285]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[546,635,260,285]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" unit="km" value="250.0">250 km</quantity>
North-West of the 
<typeStatus box="[858,906,261,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[1041,1214,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tshakaranus">
<emphasis box="[1041,1214,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. tshakaranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.) all specimens are light coloured with reduced black pattern (
<figureCitation box="[641,740,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 98 – 131" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[207,1369,202,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[186,1376,193,1873]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 98 – 131. Hephathus spp., face. 98 – 106 ― H. nanus (Herrich-Schäffer) (100 ― specimen from Bavaria); 107 – 121 ― H. freyi (Fieber) (115 – 121 ― large specimens from Iran and Central Tien-Shan, Kyrgyzstan); 122 – 131 ― H. achilleae Mityaev (124, 128 ― paratypes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244512/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,740,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="107.0">107</number>
</figureCitation>
), but in body length (3.3–3.6 mm) they are somewhat larger than typical 
<taxonomicName box="[289,374,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[289,374,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, it is impossible to distinguish between these two forms in size and coloration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Investigation of calling signals of large dark coloured males from Central Tien Shan (
<number box="[1181,1196,368,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="2.0">2</number>
individuals from the environs of Suu-Samyr Village and 
<number box="[561,575,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="6.0">6</number>
individuals from Kekemeren River Valley, 
<figureCitation box="[1074,1253,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[212,1380,204,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[183,1398,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 34. Hephathus spp., oscillograms of male calling signals. 20 – 21, 26 – 28 ― H. nanus (Herrich-Schäffer); 22 – 24, 29 – 30 ― H. freyi (Fieber); 25, 31 – 34 ― H. achilleae Mityaev." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244510/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Figs. 
<number box="[1138,1253,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="23.65" valueMax="24.3" valueMin="23.0">23–24, 30</number>
</figureCitation>
) showed that in acoustic traits they do not differ from typical 
<taxonomicName box="[696,785,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[696,785,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. freyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other regions of Central Asia, Transcaucasia and European 
<collectingCountry box="[266,341,476,501]" name="Russia" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[356,495,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 34" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[212,1380,204,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[183,1398,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 34. Hephathus spp., oscillograms of male calling signals. 20 – 21, 26 – 28 ― H. nanus (Herrich-Schäffer); 22 – 24, 29 – 30 ― H. freyi (Fieber); 25, 31 – 34 ― H. achilleae Mityaev." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244510/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
Figs. 
<number box="[420,495,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="22.29">22, 29</number>
</figureCitation>
). On this basis we establish the synonymy 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber, 1868" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1868" box="[980,1233,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freyi">
<emphasis box="[980,1065,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. freyi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fieber" box="[1081,1225,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Fieber, F. X. (1868) Europaische neue oder wenig bekannte Bythoscopida. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 18, 449 - 464." type="journal article" year="1868">
Fieber, 
<number box="[1168,1225,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1868.0">1868</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Dlabola, 1957" authorityName="Dlabola" authorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hephathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tshakaranus">
<emphasis box="[1264,1436,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">H. tshakaranus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[151,313,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Dlabola, J. (1957) Die Zikaden Afghanistans (Homopt. - Auchenorrhyncha) nach den Ergebnissen der von Herrn J. Klapperich in der Jahren 1952 - 1953 nach Afghanistan unternomminen Expeditionen. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 47, 265 - 303." type="journal article" year="1957">
Dlabola, 
<number box="[254,313,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="1957.0">1957</number>
